The members of these collegia were likewise called sodales, at all events at a later time127, and had their periodical meetings and common sacra and their own statutes. The foundation of such corporations may be traced back to the period anterior to the abolition of the monarchy128. In course of time we read of these unions occupying the public places of Rome in times of great excitement and threatening disturbance of social order ; hence in B.C. 6812⁹ a decr-ee of the senate was passed limiting the right of combination of the lower classes and suppressing such associa- tions as were judged to be mischievous and hurtful to the state.
